pl.zankowski.yahoofinanceapi

Interface DataReceiver


  • public interface DataReceiver

    Date: 19.09.2015

    Interface providing methods called when Yahoo Finance API will deliver appropriate data. To handle delivered data you need to create implementation of this interface and pass it to Session class.

    Author:
    Wojciech Zankowski

      • onIntradayReceived

        void onIntradayReceived(int requestID,
                        long timestamp,
                        double close,
                        double high,
                        double low,
                        double open,
                        int volume)

        Method streams appropriate intraday events from Yahoo Finance API.

        Parameters:
        requestID - Same as RequestID provided to Session.reqIntradayData(int, Contract) call.
        timestamp - Intraday timestamp.
        close - Intraday close price.
        high - Intraday highest price.
        low - Intraday lowest price.
        open - Intraday open price.
        volume - Intraday volume.

      • onHistoricalReceived

        void onHistoricalReceived(int requestID,
                          java.time.LocalDate date,
                          double close,
                          double high,
                          double low,
                          double open,
                          int volume,
                          double adjustedClose)

        Method streams appropriate historical events from Yahoo Finance API.

        Parameters:
        requestID - Same as RequestID provided to Session.reqHistoricalData(int, Contract, LocalDate, LocalDate, TimePeriod) call.
        date - Historical data date.
        close - Historical close price.
        high - Historical period highest price.
        low - Historical period lowest price.
        open - Historical period open price.
        volume - Historical volume.
        adjustedClose - Historical period adjusted close price.

      • onCustomReceived

        void onCustomReceived(int requestID,
                      java.util.List<java.lang.String> value)

        Method provides appropriate values from Yahoo Finance API called in Session.reqCustomData(int, String, String, int) method. Data is passed in List of String objects.

        Parameters:
        requestID - Same as RequestID provided to Session.reqCustomData(int, String, String, int) call.
        value - List of requested values.

      • onForexReceived

        void onForexReceived(int requestID,
                     long timestamp,
                     double price)

        Method provides Forex data from Yahoo Finance API.

        Parameters:
        requestID - Same as RequestID provided to Session.reqForexData(int, ForexCurrency, ForexCurrency, int) call.
        timestamp - Forex currency pair timestamp.
        price - Forex currency pair price.
